      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i get there are two sides, but isn't it kinda obvious that what people call \"woke\" is just basically just people trying to be more inclusive? it feels like the \"censorship\" argument is just used to shut down people talking about important stuff. don't you think the movement is more about progress than actually silencing anyone?",
